body:
Firstly, thank you to everyone that has worked on this project. I find myself in a situation where i need to pull docker images from within a docker container without any privileges.

I'm trying to compare local images against remote registry. I have working code for the docker-py bindings, but I'm getting different hashes back from the podman-py bindings.

I would like to call this endpoint `http+docker://localhost/v1.43/distribution/ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:latest/json`, which I can do via docker-py, but I cannot find an equivalent in podman-py.
```
>>> docker_image = "ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:latest"
>>> docker_client.api.inspect_distribution(docker_image)
{
  'Descriptor': {
    'mediaType': 'application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json', 
    'digest': 'sha256:11d59de1ea458a6acd6ae729d955494f4dc467a726a98a53602daa238557c3f1', // this is the "parent" id
    'size': 855
}, 
  'Platforms': [{'architecture': 'amd64', 'os': 'linux'}, {'architecture': 'unknown', 'os': 'unknown'}]
}
```
Alternatively, what do I need to feed client.api.get() in order to get the parent `11d59...` hash:

![image](https://github.com/containers/podman-py/assets/22226349/5a45a060-f180-4db3-bb06-30d264d8bd94)

I can get it for the *local* image (although i guess I have to just pick the first RepoDigest? is that deterministic?):
```
>>> podman_client.images.get(docker_image).attrs
{
  'Id': 'bb998df69a4aaf40ec6790bc563a162cf9b63934f4e551a3123914c32389344a', 
  'Digest': 'sha256:11d59de1ea458a6acd6ae729d955494f4dc467a726a98a53602daa238557c3f1', 
  'RepoTags': ['ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:latest'], 
  'RepoDigests': ['ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114@sha256:11d59de1ea458a6acd6ae729d955494f4dc467a726a98a53602daa238557c3f1', 'ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114@sha256:b4185bd52d9cc53deecc9ee24c44a036b3613cf94edc592bfb2b84be87fd156f'], 
  'Parent': '', 
  'Comment': 'buildkit.dockerfile.v0', 
  'Created': '2023-09-14T10:36:34.421474411Z', 
  'Config': {'Env': ['PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin'], 'WorkingDir': '/'}, 'Version': '', 'Author': '', 'Architecture': 'amd64', 'Os': 'linux', 'Size': 4736225, 'VirtualSize': 4736225, 'GraphDriver': {'Name': 'vfs', 'Data': None}, 'RootFS': {'Type': 'layers', 'Layers': ['sha256:93b4c624abaa80b865bf220210c08d445c2c6381f1bb27ca7fa114b0b4257b56']}, 'Labels': None, 'Annotations': {}, 'ManifestType': 'application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json', 'User': '', 'History': [{'created': '2023-09-14T10:36:34.421474411Z', 'created_by': 'COPY /compilers /compilers # buildkit', 'comment': 'buildkit.dockerfile.v0'}], 'NamesHistory': ['ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:latest']}
```
but I can't seem to get it remotely:
```
>>> podman_client.manifests.get(docker_image).attrs
{
  'schemaVersion': 2, 
  'mediaType': 'application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json', 
  'manifests': [
  {
    'mediaType': 'application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json', 
    'size': 480, 
    'digest': 'sha256:b4185bd52d9cc53deecc9ee24c44a036b3613cf94edc592bfb2b84be87fd156f', 
    'platform': {'architecture': 'amd64', 'os': 'linux'}
  }, 
  {
    'mediaType': 'application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json', 
    'size': 566, 
    'digest': 'sha256:b6cabbe8342853fbe9c0a367bad2632356840b251337c4c51735b03a3c4041e0', 
    'platform': {'architecture': 'unknown', 'os': 'unknown'}
  }
  ], 
    'names': 'ghcr.io/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:latest'
}
```
Is there a different method I can use?


**Edit**:

Following on from this, I'm trying to extract the value out of ghcr.io's V2 API. but it seems futile. Their API does not seem to support the 'fat' manifest (`application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json`), only the `oci` ones (`application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json`). Which means I am really confused as to how Docker is managing to pull that digest (even podman pulls out the 'fat' manifest *list*).

```json
$ export TOKEN=$(curl --silent https://ghcr.io/token\?scope\="repository:mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114:pull" | jq --raw-output .token)
$ curl --silent  -H "Accept: application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json"   -H "Accept: application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json"   -H "Accept: application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json"   -H "Accept: application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json"   -H "Authorization: Bearer ${TOKEN}"   https://ghcr.io/v2/mkst/compilers/nds_arm9/mwcc_30_114/manifests/latest | jq
{
